      "title": "Define a class with an instance variable",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "question_text": "Which of the following correctly defines a Python class with an instance variable 'name'?",
      "options": {
        "A": "class Student: name = 'John'",
        "B": "class Student: def __init__(self): self.name = 'John'",
        "C": "class Student: def init(self): name = 'John'",
        "D": "def Student(): self.name = 'John'"
